*Usage of ARICHDatabase.py steering file*

//////// How to run steering file

To run steering file you must provide 2 arguments:

1.) READING/WRITING OPTION
Choose option for reading/storing data:
    Wagel      // storing aerogel data to DB - class ARICHAerogelInfo
    Ragel      // reading aerogel from DB - class ARICHAerogelInfo
    WhapdQA    // storing HAPD QA data to DB - class ARICHHapdQA
    RhapdQA    // reading HAPD QA data from DB - class ARICHAHapdQA
    Wasic      // storing ASIC data to DB - class ARICHAsicInfo
    Rasic      // reading ASIC data from DB - class ARICHAsicInfo

    Following option is not working yet:
    WhapdInfo  // storing HAPD and HAPD chip data to DB - classes ARICHHapdInfo, ARICHHapdChipInfo

2.) GLOBAL TAG
Make sure to use same global tag for storing and reading same data to/from DB. This is very important for Rasic that has multiple payloads for one class.

//////// Accessing the data

Root/xml files can be found:
1.) aerogel (xml files)
1st measurement: https://belle2.cc.kek.jp/svn/groups/arich/database/data/aerogel/
2nd measurement: http://www-f9.ijs.si/~manca/DBdata/aerogelData/

2.) hapdQA (root files) - for now, only one root file is available
http://www-f9.ijs.si/~manca/DBdata/hapdQAdata/

3.) asics (root files)
asicData.tar.gz at http://www-f9.ijs.si/~manca/DBdata/asicData/

4.) hapd info (xls files; converted to xml files - check README file at https://belle2.cc.kek.jp/browse/viewvc.cgi/svn/groups/arich/database/README?revision=13763&view=markup ); xml files available also at: http://www-f9.ijs.si/~manca/DBdata/hapdInfoData/

